title: @OspreyMTEN Doubles Duo Advances at Saint Francis Health System ITA All-American Championships
text: registered a two-set victory during the Round of 64 in Doubles Qualifying at the Saint Francis Health System ITA All-American Championships on Tuesday evening. Findel-Hawkins and Zuern claimed a 7-5, 6-1 win over Wichita State's Miroslav Herzan and Haru Inoue. The duo, who are ranked No. 9-16 in Qualifying Doubles, advance to Tuesday's Round of 32 and face TCU's Hudson Blake and Trevor Johnson. Winner of that match plays again later on Tuesday in the Round of 16 against the winner of the match between Florida's McClain Kessler and Alfredo Perez and New Mexico's Hayden Sabatka and Bart Van Leijsen, who are the round's No. 2 seed. Meanwhile, also on Tuesday, Zuern played his Qualifying Singles consolation match, falling 6-4, 3-6, 6-3 to Richardo Jorge from Ole Miss. Out of Zuern's six singles matches played at the tournament, four went to three sets. Doubles action continues for Findel-Hawkins and Zuern at 2 p.m., EST/1 p.m., CST on Wednesday.
